      <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\gpio\trident_gpio_overview.xml" xtrc="body:2;33:27">
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\gpio\trident_gpio_overview.xml" xtrc="p:2;36:24">Switchtec firmware supports four kinds of GPIO adapters: on-chip GPIOs, GPIO Expanders, SGPIO streams, and virtual GPIO. These adapters represent GPIO pin sources, where logical GPIO elements are mapped to local GPIOs as well as GPIOs behind GPIO Expanders.</p>
         <fig class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\gpio\trident_gpio_overview.xml" xtrc="fig:1;39:28">
